column5: First ice trout is tough to beat!  Better late than never...6-8 feet in log jams"I should be able to park my sled on the ice no problems"...Set up a bunch of brookie boobie traps around this submerged tree where most of the fish came off of...The spoils...
Sweet. A pic of pink fillets, frying, would of been a bonus.
Sweet. A pic of pink fillets, frying, would of been a bonus. Sorry I forgot...:burp:
Wow. Nice haul bud. Great start to the year.
Boobie traps, Hahaha  Kick'n butt as usual Joey, good report!
Nice haul there Joey , love the backwoods reports . My kind of fishing
Christ I have bad timing. We should have walked that extra 200 meters last week
Beauts!
Nice report Joey!!!
Nice looking fish!  Thanx!
I really want to go fishing now...wish we had just a bit more ice
Nice haul!  Looks like a great day!
You live in a piece of paradise, beautiful surroundings, awesome catch, good on ya
Man that is awesome! I'm not as big on ice fishing as I used to be but that is something I'd love to do.
It's a totally unique experience, one of my favorite fishing styles, but can also be extremely frustrating!
You live in a piece of paradise, beautiful surroundings, awesome catch, good on ya I agree.Those are some nice chunky specks! Yum Yum.
Nice! What a great day
Awesome Joey !!!!!!!
Nice fish!
Nice going can't believe I missed this one I may take a drive to a favourite speck lake this weekend, if cooks isn't solid
Live minnows?  BEAUTY fish!  Doug
Yes, live minnows, my buddy got the biggest one sight fishing a lipless rattle bait.
Big average size. Did you guys get any mini's or just those chunkers?
No minis, smallest was 14.5" and biggest right around 20.
Sorry I forgot...:burp:  LOLOLOL.  Nice one guysâ€¦.those are bayooootees.
